meanings.definition: To sing with trills, runs, or other melodic embellishments.
meanings.sent1: The bird warbled a beautiful tune in the morning.
meanings.sent2: She warbled a sweet melody at the talent show.
meanings.sent3: The cat warbled along with the music, trying to mimic the sound.
meanings.sent4: The wind warbled through the trees, creating a symphony of nature.
meanings.sent5: His voice warbled with emotion as he sang the heartfelt song.

meanings.definition: A melodious sound produced by a bird.
meanings.sent1: The warbled of the robin filled the garden with music.
meanings.sent2: We woke up to the cheerful warbled of the songbirds outside.
meanings.sent3: The warbled of the parrot made everyone in the room burst into laughter.
meanings.sent4: The warbled of the nightingale seemed to echo through the entire forest.
meanings.sent5: The warbled of the canary was so soothing, it put everyone at ease.
